Interface ISensorRepositorySpringData

All Superinterfaces:
org.springframework.data.repository.CrudRepository<SensorDataModel, String>, org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository<SensorDataModel, String>, org.springframework.data.repository.ListCrudRepository<SensorDataModel, String>, org.springframework.data.repository.ListPagingAndSortingRepository<SensorDataModel, String>, org.springframework.data.repository.PagingAndSortingRepository<SensorDataModel, String>, org.springframework.data.repository.query.QueryByExampleExecutor<SensorDataModel>, org.springframework.data.repository.Repository<SensorDataModel, String>
public interface ISensorRepositorySpringData extends org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository<SensorDataModel,String>
This is a Spring Data JPA repository for SensorDataModel entities. It extends JpaRepository, which provides JPA related methods like save(), findOne(), findAll(), count(), delete() etc. It can be used to perform database operations on SensorDataModel entities.

SensorDataModel is the entity that this repository works with. String is the type of the primary key of the SensorDataModel entity.

    • findSensorsByDeviceId

      List<SensorDataModel> findSensorsByDeviceId (String identity)
      This method retrieves all SensorDataModel entities associated with a specific DeviceId from the repository. It takes the identity of a DeviceId as a parameter and returns a list of SensorDataModel entities associated with that DeviceId. The identity is a string representation of the DeviceId.
      Parameters:
      identity - The device id.
      Returns:
      A list of SensorDataModel entities associated with the provided DeviceId.
